						 <strong>6 modern business niches.</strong><p><span>  </span></p><figure><div><div></div><div><img></div><div></div></div><meta><figcaption><span></span></figcaption></figure><p><span>When I publish some business ideas, constantly someone writes a comment, well, it's old, newer, newer. And I decided to make a list of modern trends in which startups are created by those who want to have it is a modern business.</span></p><p><span>1. The most popular topic is the development and implementation of artificial intelligence. All new Internet startups work in one way or another with artificial intelligence. Artificial intelligence is being implemented in all spheres: education, trade, banking, entertainment. Modern start-up unthinkable without artificial intelligence.</span></p><p><span>2. Development of the virtual environment. Virtual reality is actually an existing and working technology. But, as was once the case with the Internet, it still has relatively little content. Gradually, the virtual environment will evolve in the same way that the Internet has evolved.</span></p><p><span>3. Robotics. Robots are already a reality. Practically all over the world, robots work in enterprises. Now robots are being introduced to serve the public in banks and other areas. In addition, robots are actively being introduced into the everyday environment. And this trend will only continue grow.</span></p><figure><div><div></div><div><img></div><div></div></div><meta><figcaption><span></span></figcaption></figure><p><span>4. Electric charging stations. For several years, startups in Europe and the United States have been deploying networks of electric gas stations, as the fleet of electric vehicles is growing and will grow more and more.</span></p><p><span>5. recycling of garbage and using it for production. Already in in many countries, plastic is recycled and turned into building materials. But it's not just about plastic, all other waste goes into business too. And although this niche has been working for a long time, on the other hand, the rest of the world is just a lot of garbage. Although it is actually the same raw material as oil. So this sphere is only in its own right beginning.</span></p><p><span>6. Sources of energy. The topic of economical energy consumption is very relevant. Of course, the topic of wind turbines, solar panels and water desalination plants is already old. But now actively developed and popular technologies that make mining the cheapest and most efficient productive.</span></p><p><span>Success!</span></p><blockquote><span><b>Please like it, it's easy for you, but it's nice for us.</b></span></blockquote><blockquote><span>Denial of responsibility. Everything stated in this article is the thoughts and ideas of the author. This publication should not be considered a recommendation or any other type of incentive to action. The author withdraws from assume all responsibility for any negative consequences, risks and losses, if you decide to put what you have read into practice. </span></blockquote><blockquote><span><b>Click the subscribe button and our articles will always be at hand.</b></span></blockquote><div></div>
